Call for you.

514
00:39:56,343 --> 00:39:57,530
Hello, this is Kasahara

515
00:40:00,561 --> 00:40:01,381
Machida?

516
00:40:02,731 --> 00:40:06,611
Did you get a reply telegram?
Tsuneko-san is sure she took the Hakuba train.

517
00:40:09,479 --> 00:40:10,305
Tsuneko-san was dead...?

518
00:40:14,600 --> 00:40:17,680
She's Tsuneko-san for sure.

519
00:40:24,505 --> 00:40:29,151
Then Tsuneko Saito, the victim...
Tsuneko Saito was going straight to Shinjuku?

520
00:40:31,447 --> 00:40:34,247
But she got off at Tachikawa Station.

521
00:40:36,080 --> 00:40:38,167
The crime scene is near Yanoguchi Station on the Nambu Line.

522
00:40:39,358 --> 00:40:42,352
Maybe the victim knew someone there.

523
00:40:42,971 --> 00:40:47,391
But Tsuneko knew I was coming to Shinjuku Station to pick her up.

524
00:40:48,230 --> 00:40:50,463
I didn't think she got off at Tachikawa Station.

525
00:40:50,577 --> 00:40:54,117
I see.
Someone must have gotten her off at Tachikawa Station.

526
00:40:55,127 --> 00:41:00,234
And is it not conceivable that the Nanbu Line took him from Tachikawa Station to Yannoguchi Station, which is even closer to the site?

527
00:41:00,375 --> 00:41:02,622
No, the victim never got off at Yanokuchi Station.

528
00:41:03,640 --> 00:41:05,834
No one at the station claims to have seen her.

529
00:41:11,330 --> 00:41:16,803
He's been making strange phone calls to you.
That means the killer knows we're on to him.

530
00:41:17,988 --> 00:41:22,835
That's right.
Ms. Tsuneko was killed because I called her.

531
00:41:23,991 --> 00:41:28,597
He's so bad.
Maybe you should be careful for a few days.

532
00:41:32,506 --> 00:41:35,573
I'll do whatever it takes to find out who did it.

533
00:41:36,413 --> 00:41:38,526
If I don't, I'll feel bad for Ms. Tsuneko.

534
00:41:39,784 --> 00:41:43,130
But if anything should happen to you...

535
00:41:48,194 --> 00:41:51,414
Don't worry.
I have a mascot for good luck.

536
00:41:51,687 --> 00:41:52,827
Mascot for good luck?

537
00:41:54,097 --> 00:41:57,177
It's really supposed to protect me.

538
00:41:57,831 --> 00:41:58,457
Funny?

539
00:42:00,263 --> 00:42:00,977
No.

540
00:42:02,397 --> 00:42:03,510
Don't laugh?

541
00:42:09,311 --> 00:42:10,011
I'm not laughing.

542
00:42:11,585 --> 00:42:13,945
I'll give you one.

543
00:42:16,669 --> 00:42:19,842
You have to be careful too.

544
00:42:22,137 --> 00:42:23,691
Thank you.

545
00:42:26,370 --> 00:42:27,343
Train is coming.

546
00:42:35,527 --> 00:42:36,120
Hi.

547
00:42:37,626 --> 00:42:40,080
What a incident.

548
00:42:40,163 --> 00:42:42,797
Same here.
Where have you been?

549
00:42:43,318 --> 00:42:44,638
Martial Arts Garden

550
00:42:45,050 --> 00:42:47,710
I haven't sketched in a while.

551
00:42:49,045 --> 00:42:51,238
Is the seat free?

552
00:42:52,229 --> 00:42:55,182
Someone was sitting here.
Maybe he went to the bathroom.

553
00:42:55,768 --> 00:42:58,361
I'm here again.

554
00:43:18,740 --> 00:43:19,949
Who's that woman now?

555
00:43:20,509 --> 00:43:23,342
She's a girl for Uno.
Her name is Machiko.

556
00:43:24,414 --> 00:43:27,934
So Tsurumaki wasn't traveling alone.

557
00:43:28,665 --> 00:43:29,298
Why?

558
00:43:30,117 --> 00:43:33,610
Tsurumaki is like Uno's boss.

559
00:43:34,644 --> 00:43:39,271
Of course he knows.
How can he be sitting in the same car with that woman, sitting so far away from her?

560
00:43:43,655 --> 00:43:44,902
How about this theory?

561
00:43:45,962 --> 00:43:48,962
He was sitting side by side with her until Tachikawa.

562
00:43:49,816 --> 00:43:54,536
But when he saw us, he said, "This is a bad idea.
She was the only one who moved to the back.

563
00:44:01,401 --> 00:44:02,494
It must be so.

564
00:44:03,336 --> 00:44:06,422
I bet they're sitting side by side right now.

565
00:44:25,289 --> 00:44:25,996
What's wrong?

566
00:44:27,552 --> 00:44:31,985
I was thinking that Machida-san's reasoning earlier applies to my sister.

567
00:44:32,373 --> 00:44:37,086
I see.
That's why your sister moved to the back of the bus in Hamamatsu.

568
00:44:38,398 --> 00:44:39,438
But if that's the case.

569
00:44:40,113 --> 00:44:45,213
Your sister, her companion, and someone who knew them both boarded the bus.

570
00:44:46,427 --> 00:44:47,754
A bit too coincidental, don't you think?

571
00:44:48,177 --> 00:44:51,504
But the coincidence is real right now.

572
00:44:52,520 --> 00:44:55,587
Let's get that woman and find out what his alibi is.

573
00:44:59,399 --> 00:45:00,019
Tell me.

574
00:45:02,134 --> 00:45:04,601
It's Christmas.
Don't tell me you've forgotten.

575
00:45:06,257 --> 00:45:09,071
If MADAM gets to know, I won't be able to stay in here.

576
00:45:09,674 --> 00:45:10,541
I won't be able to do my sewing.

577
00:45:10,768 --> 00:45:12,268
We won't tell anyone.

578
00:45:13,351 --> 00:45:15,684
Just answer if you were with Tsurumaki on Christmas Eve.

579
00:45:17,261 --> 00:45:18,374
I went to Atami.

580
00:45:19,049 --> 00:45:19,769
With him.

581
00:45:19,916 --> 00:45:21,849
You sure?
Where were you at 12?

582
00:45:22,935 --> 00:45:25,055
Take a bath at the inn in Atami

583
00:45:25,616 --> 00:45:28,149
I'll check with the inn and see if you're lying.

584
00:45:28,529 --> 00:45:29,336
Trust me.

585
00:45:37,275 --> 00:45:37,835
Go home.

586
00:45:38,719 --> 00:45:41,699
I won't tell Madam, so please don't tell Tsurumaki about today.

587
00:45:42,127 --> 00:45:44,235
I'm sorry about that.

588
00:45:44,836 --> 00:45:45,842
I'll take this.

589
00:45:46,447 --> 00:45:47,167
Here you go.

590
00:45:49,859 --> 00:45:50,805
All clean.

591
00:45:51,665 --> 00:45:52,852
How is this possible?

592
00:45:53,385 --> 00:45:53,985
Wait a minute.

593
00:45:54,857 --> 00:46:05,357
You, me and Tsuneko Saito's family were the only ones who knew she was coming to Tokyo on the Hakuba train yesterday.

594
00:46:05,757 --> 00:46:06,510
There's someone else.

595
00:46:06,737 --> 00:46:07,117
Who?

596
00:46:07,921 --> 00:46:08,841
The woman in the apartment.

597
00:46:25,524 --> 00:46:26,538
Did something happen?

598
00:46:26,563 --> 00:46:29,017
The caretaker's aunt was killed in a car accident.

599
00:46:29,130 --> 00:46:29,630
Hello?

600
00:46:29,786 --> 00:46:33,642
She got pulled over right out front.

601
00:46:34,191 --> 00:46:35,118
It was around 5:00.

602
00:46:35,417 --> 00:46:38,777
I was just passing by and I got the license plate number right.

603
00:46:39,269 --> 00:46:44,096
But the police found that the car with the license plate number was driving somewhere else.

604
00:46:44,664 --> 00:46:47,357
It was a fake license plate number.

605
00:46:47,664 --> 00:46:49,171
Police said same.

606
00:46:49,196 --> 00:46:50,717
Do you remember what the car looked like?

607
00:46:50,958 --> 00:46:53,125
Polices asked me same things.

608
00:46:53,771 --> 00:46:57,311
It was dark, and I only focused the number.

609
00:46:58,261 --> 00:47:00,074
But I'm pretty sure it was a mid-size car.

610
00:47:00,284 --> 00:47:02,484
It was a mid-size car.
Are you sure?

611
00:47:03,301 --> 00:47:05,468
Everyone else who saw it said so, too.

612
00:47:06,361 --> 00:47:07,821
Are you newspaper reporter?

613
00:47:08,141 --> 00:47:08,627
Yes.

614
00:47:10,458 --> 00:47:11,811
Wanna take a rest?

615
00:47:12,705 --> 00:47:17,591
Find someone who can drive a mid-size car.

616
00:47:18,569 --> 00:47:21,503
Saito Tsuneko and my sis must have been taken there in that car.

617
00:47:22,500 --> 00:47:25,733
The hit-and-run on the woman in the apartment must have been planned by that guy.

618
00:47:27,785 --> 00:47:28,571
Why would he do that?

619
00:47:28,898 --> 00:47:32,545
He used her as a spy to protect himself.

620
00:47:33,254 --> 00:47:38,134
But he already killed TSUNEKO.
When there was nothing she could do, he killed her to keep her quiet.

621
00:47:46,531 --> 00:47:47,104
Yoshii

622
00:47:48,824 --> 00:47:50,217
Ah, seniority.

623
00:47:51,364 --> 00:47:53,004
Do you have something to be guilty about?

624
00:47:53,237 --> 00:47:54,024
No, I don't.

625
00:47:55,607 --> 00:47:57,887
The Weekly Times circulation seems to be up quite a bit.

626
00:47:58,231 --> 00:47:59,997
Well, thanks to you.

627
00:48:01,285 --> 00:48:04,405
You've got a reputation for being the top story there.

628
00:48:13,239 --> 00:48:15,406
Machida,Sorry I'm late.

629
00:48:15,616 --> 00:48:20,163
I found out.
Nishiaki is the only one of the four who has a medium size car.

630
00:48:20,446 --> 00:48:21,346
How about Seno?

631
00:48:21,626 --> 00:48:23,673
He doesn't have one.
He's got a license, though.

632
00:48:24,503 --> 00:48:27,103
So Dr. Nishiaki is the one who pulled you over yesterday?

633
00:48:27,307 --> 00:48:29,287
That's the thing...
Strange thing is...

634
00:48:30,314 --> 00:48:33,048
Nishiaki took a cab to and from the hospital yesterday.

635
00:48:35,431 --> 00:48:37,104
He left the hospital in a cab around 4:00.

636
00:48:38,190 --> 00:48:41,023
The woman was attracted to a mid-size car with a fake license plate around 5:00.

637
00:48:42,295 --> 00:48:46,509
So somewhere along the way, he got out of the cab and into his own car.
It all fits together.

638
00:48:50,496 --> 00:48:53,343
I'll see what I can find out about his behavior yesterday.

639
00:48:57,516 --> 00:49:00,283
I didn't expect you to ask me out.

640
00:49:01,003 --> 00:49:03,403
I was frustrated about my job.

641
00:49:03,835 --> 00:49:06,788
I'm sure with someone like you, I'll be able to find some relief and distraction.

642
00:49:07,615 --> 00:49:09,121
You've changed.

643
00:49:09,278 --> 00:49:12,471
No way.
I kind of want to be a punk.

644
00:49:12,944 --> 00:49:15,624
No, no, no. I'm saying you're becoming more and more attractive.

645
00:49:16,406 --> 00:49:17,093
Hello?

646
00:49:21,868 --> 00:49:23,268
Fake culturist.

647
00:49:27,905 --> 00:49:29,251
You have to be careful with that guy.

648
00:49:33,252 --> 00:49:35,112
He's play boy.

649
00:49:35,845 --> 00:49:36,618
No way.

650
00:49:39,455 --> 00:49:40,655
No, it's true.

651
00:49:41,179 --> 00:49:44,352
There was a woman who came to me, asking me to take care of his children.

652
00:49:48,452 --> 00:49:51,359
The one who was close to you.

653
00:49:53,682 --> 00:49:57,515
You mean she was my sister?

654
00:50:03,886 --> 00:50:06,252
No way.

655
00:50:07,129 --> 00:50:09,196
He just loved your sis.

656
00:50:10,315 --> 00:50:14,275
Machida didn't think much of your sister.

657
00:50:17,026 --> 00:50:20,166
Sachiko, I want you to dance with you.

658
00:50:20,973 --> 00:50:21,639
Kasahara,.

659
00:50:24,117 --> 00:50:27,051
Go home.
I'll send you.

660
00:50:34,071 --> 00:50:35,458
Nice car, isn't it?

661
00:50:36,398 --> 00:50:37,538
First time?

662
00:50:39,950 --> 00:50:44,050
It's a domestic car.
If I had the money, I'd trade it in for a foreign car.

663
00:50:44,482 --> 00:50:46,849
You drove this car to the hospital every day?

664
00:50:47,522 --> 00:50:47,935
Yeah.

665
00:50:53,872 --> 00:50:56,166
Yesterday you took a cab.

666
00:50:57,901 --> 00:51:00,941
Yesterday my car broke down and I had to take it to the shop.

667
00:51:01,609 --> 00:51:07,202
He's my family repairman.
If I leave it there for half a day, they'll take care of it.

668
00:51:09,576 --> 00:51:10,570
Is it in your neighborhood?

669
00:51:33,356 --> 00:51:34,023
Damn it.

670
00:51:34,663 --> 00:51:35,369
What's wrong?

671
00:51:36,313 --> 00:51:37,233
It's broken.

672
00:52:38,687 --> 00:52:39,400
It's fixed.

673
00:52:53,365 --> 00:52:56,518
I've been having a little trouble with the engine lately.

674
00:53:06,522 --> 00:53:07,162
Well..

675
00:53:09,788 --> 00:53:11,755
It's still early. Let's go have a drink somewhere.

676
00:53:12,521 --> 00:53:14,695
I know good restaurant.

677
00:53:16,558 --> 00:53:17,411
But..

678
00:53:19,484 --> 00:53:19,984
Let's go.

679
00:53:32,029 --> 00:53:33,269
Let go of me!

680
00:53:35,209 --> 00:53:36,516
Stop it!

681
00:53:38,076 --> 00:53:38,996
Let go of me!

682
00:53:40,113 --> 00:53:41,267
Let go of me!

683
00:54:00,244 --> 00:54:01,844
I'd hate for you to get the wrong idea.

684
00:54:02,823 --> 00:54:03,984
I think I was joking too much.

685
00:54:04,643 --> 00:54:07,283
You think I'm the kind of person who would seriously do something like this?

686
00:54:30,448 --> 00:54:31,041
Good night.

687
00:55:06,709 --> 00:55:07,349
Who?

688
00:55:07,879 --> 00:55:08,492
It's me.

689
00:55:09,939 --> 00:55:10,725
Oh right.

690
00:55:14,871 --> 00:55:17,424
It's late.
Where did you go?

691
00:55:17,564 --> 00:55:19,124
At a nightclub.
Yokohama.

692
00:55:19,364 --> 00:55:19,924
That's it?

693
00:55:20,184 --> 00:55:20,824
Yes, that's it.

694
00:55:21,972 --> 00:55:23,518
Nishiaki was so scary.

695
00:55:23,905 --> 00:55:24,925
What's wrong with Nishiaki?

696
00:55:26,395 --> 00:55:27,322
Tell me.

697
00:55:27,957 --> 00:55:31,451
I didn't tell you.
No matter what happens, I have a mascot.

698
00:55:31,973 --> 00:55:35,620
Damn it..Nishiaki.
Did you find out anything about the car?

699
00:55:36,272 --> 00:55:39,959
He said his car broke down yesterday and he had to take it to the shop.

700
00:55:40,112 --> 00:55:40,493
where?

701
00:55:40,872 --> 00:55:43,038
I heard it's his family's shop.

702
00:55:44,144 --> 00:55:44,910
Wanna come in?

703
00:55:45,210 --> 00:55:46,837
Anyway, I'm gonna check out this factory.

704
00:55:47,114 --> 00:55:47,954
Now?

705
00:55:48,253 --> 00:55:49,627
The sooner the better.

706
00:55:58,826 --> 00:56:00,499
No repairs.

707
00:56:01,140 --> 00:56:02,927
I hope you didn't take it to another factory.

708
00:56:02,952 --> 00:56:03,841
Not at all.

709
00:56:04,438 --> 00:56:07,318
We've been repairing Dr. Nishiaki's car for a long time.

710
00:56:07,805 --> 00:56:11,925
One phone call and we're on the road.
We've been taking care of him for a long time.

711
00:56:12,624 --> 00:56:13,184
I see.

712
00:56:38,711 --> 00:56:41,497
Seno loved your sister.

713
00:56:42,237 --> 00:56:46,703
Machida didn't think much of your sister.

714
01:00:29,066 --> 01:00:29,713
Who?

715
01:00:30,026 --> 01:00:31,799
The door was open.

716
01:00:34,900 --> 01:00:37,833
I'm the caretaker now, coming on behalf of my sister.

717
01:01:04,267 --> 01:01:05,020
That car.

718
01:01:07,119 --> 01:01:09,359
You said it looked like Nishiaki's car?

719
01:01:10,588 --> 01:01:12,971
It was too dark to make out but..

720
01:01:12,996 --> 01:01:15,830
Then I guess Nishiaki is the culprit after all.

721
01:01:16,314 --> 01:01:18,986
It was a complete lie that he went to his family's repair shop.

722
01:01:19,549 --> 01:01:25,330
But your sister was murdered on Christmas Eve.
Dr. Nishiaki has an alibi, right?

723
01:01:25,432 --> 01:01:32,424
That's the thing. I spent all night last night trying to figure it out.
The final conclusion I came to was that he had an accomplice.

724
01:01:32,827 --> 01:01:35,359
Who's an accomplice?

725
01:01:35,945 --> 01:01:40,108
Someone who can drive.
I mean, Seno.

726
01:01:40,632 --> 01:01:44,968
Well, they don't seem to get along.
They're always bad-mouthing each other.

727
01:01:45,335 --> 01:01:49,335
That's what's suspicious.
They could be making it look that way, but behind the scenes, they could be holding hands.

728
01:01:49,773 --> 01:01:52,999
But then again, maybe Seno has an alibi for Eve.

729
01:01:53,406 --> 01:01:54,609
At a nightclub in Yokohama.

730
01:01:54,945 --> 01:01:59,281
That's very suspicious.
Nightclubs are very crowded on Christmas Eve.

731
01:01:59,890 --> 01:02:03,351
If he leaves in the middle of the night and comes back after the crime, he won't even know what he's doing.

732
01:02:03,859 --> 01:02:04,702
I see

733
01:02:04,890 --> 01:02:06,906
I think I need to go to the hostess and check it out.

734
01:02:07,898 --> 01:02:11,827
Anyway, I'll see you soon.
I'm trying to set a trap for Nishiaki.

735
01:02:12,218 --> 01:02:12,929
What kind?

736
01:02:13,281 --> 01:02:14,515
I'll tell you at the Lunar.

737
01:02:15,085 --> 01:02:17,054
Okay.
I'll be right there.

738
01:02:19,632 --> 01:02:20,992
300,000yen.

739
01:02:21,476 --> 01:02:24,187
Machida's severance pay
She can't get it if she's killed.

740
01:02:24,249 --> 01:02:25,617
It's big money.

741
01:02:25,874 --> 01:02:27,999
If you quit tomorrow, I'll pay you a severance package.

742
01:02:28,382 --> 01:02:29,015
Oh.

743
01:02:31,054 --> 01:02:32,281
Send here.

744
01:02:32,421 --> 01:02:34,101
Her mom?

745
01:02:34,367 --> 01:02:37,304
Kotani Village, Tsuru District, Yamanashi Prefecture

746
01:02:37,499 --> 01:02:40,234
If it's okay, I'll deliver it.

747
01:02:40,390 --> 01:02:41,827
I'll see her son.

748
01:02:42,288 --> 01:02:42,718
Where?

749
01:02:42,812 --> 01:02:43,835
Right there.

750
01:02:44,007 --> 01:02:45,100
That's funny.

751
01:02:45,187 --> 01:02:45,726
for what?

752
01:02:46,070 --> 01:02:49,609
Machida's brother isn't in Tokyo.

753
01:02:49,890 --> 01:02:52,132
Yes, he is.
He's in the Times Weekly.

754
01:02:52,359 --> 01:02:54,726
What?
He's still in high school.

755
01:02:55,023 --> 01:02:56,827
Eh?
High school student?

756
01:03:00,288 --> 01:03:02,999
You saw him yesterday, too.

757
01:03:03,718 --> 01:03:04,226
Where?

758
01:03:04,820 --> 01:03:05,757
At Tsukihashi Park.

759
01:03:07,523 --> 01:03:11,609
Masami Yoshii, my junior in college.

760
01:03:11,836 --> 01:03:12,578
Oh.

761
01:03:17,246 --> 01:03:18,316
Why not?

762
01:03:18,456 --> 01:03:19,151
I won't.

763
01:03:20,301 --> 01:03:22,082
Even the case isn't closed yet.

764
01:03:22,301 --> 01:03:25,246
It's just the weekly one.
I'm having a hard time finding a top story.

765
01:03:25,707 --> 01:03:26,660
Write the article.

766
01:03:28,824 --> 01:03:31,191
